    public class DefaultServiceLoader
extends Object
implements ServiceLoader
    The default service loader allows to get service instance based on default service implementation class.

      • getService

        public <T> T getService(Class<T> service,
                        boolean singleton)
                 throws ServiceLoadingException
        Description copied from interface: ServiceLoader
        Gets the registered implementation for the given service.

        If a singleton is asked and if an instance of this service has already been created, this instance is returned. Otherwise, creates a new instance of the implementation type.

        Specified by:
        getService in interface ServiceLoader
        Type Parameters:
        T - the service type.
        Parameters:
        service - the service.
        singleton - if true returns an already created instance if any, creates a new one otherwise.
        Returns:
        an instance of the given service or null if no implementation is available.
        Throws:
        ServiceLoadingException - if an error occurs while instantiating the service implementation.

        Description copied from interface: ServiceLoader
        Gets the registered implementation for the given service. If there is no registered implementation, an instance of the default implementation is returned.

        If a singleton is asked and if an instance of this service has already been created, this instance is returned. Otherwise, creates a new instance of the implementation type.
